2950static void remove_sits_in_journal(struct f2fs_sb_info *sbi)
2951{
2952 struct curseg_info *curseg = CURSEG_I(sbi, CURSEG_COLD_DATA);
2953 struct f2fs_journal *journal = curseg->journal;
2954 int i;
2955
2956 down_write(&curseg->journal_rwsem);
2957 for (i = 0; i < sits_in_cursum(journal); i++) {
2958 unsigned int segno;
2959 bool dirtied;
2960
2961 segno = le32_to_cpu(segno_in_journal(journal, i));
2962 dirtied = __mark_sit_entry_dirty(sbi, segno);
2963
2964 if (!dirtied)
2965 add_sit_entry(segno, &SM_I(sbi)->sit_entry_set);
2966 }
2967 update_sits_in_cursum(journal, -i);
2968 up_write(&curseg->journal_rwsem);
2969}
2970
2971/*
2972 * CP calls this function, which flushes SIT entries including sit_journal,
2973 * and moves prefree segs to free segs.
2974 */
2975void flush_sit_entries(struct f2fs_sb_info *sbi, struct cp_control *cpc)
2976{
2977 struct sit_info *sit_i = SIT_I(sbi);
2978 unsigned long *bitmap = sit_i->dirty_sentries_bitmap;
2979 struct curseg_info *curseg = CURSEG_I(sbi, CURSEG_COLD_DATA);
2980 struct f2fs_journal *journal = curseg->journal;
2981 struct sit_entry_set *ses, *tmp;
2982 struct list_head *head = &SM_I(sbi)->sit_entry_set;
2983 bool to_journal = true;
2984 struct seg_entry *se;
2985
2986 mutex_lock(&sit_i->sentry_lock);
2987
2988 if (!sit_i->dirty_sentries)
2989 goto out;
2990
2991 /*
2992 * add and account sit entries of dirty bitmap in sit entry
2993 * set temporarily
2994 */
2995 add_sits_in_set(sbi);
2996
2997 /*
2998 * if there are no enough space in journal to store dirty sit
2999 * entries, remove all entries from journal and add and account
3000 * them in sit entry set.
3001 */
3002 if (!__has_cursum_space(journal, sit_i->dirty_sentries, SIT_JOURNAL))
3003 remove_sits_in_journal(sbi);
3004
3005 /*
3006 * there are two steps to flush sit entries:
3007 * #1, flush sit entries to journal in current cold data summary block.
3008 * #2, flush sit entries to sit page.
3009 */
3010 list_for_each_entry_safe(ses, tmp, head, set_list) {
3011 struct page *page = NULL;
3012 struct f2fs_sit_block *raw_sit = NULL;
3013 unsigned int start_segno = ses->start_segno;
3014 unsigned int end = min(start_segno + SIT_ENTRY_PER_BLOCK,
3015 (unsigned long)MAIN_SEGS(sbi));
3016 unsigned int segno = start_segno;
3017
3018 if (to_journal &&
3019 !__has_cursum_space(journal, ses->entry_cnt, SIT_JOURNAL))
3020 to_journal = false;
3021
3022 if (to_journal) {
3023 down_write(&curseg->journal_rwsem);
3024 } else {
3025 page = get_next_sit_page(sbi, start_segno);
3026 raw_sit = page_address(page);
3027 }
3028
3029 /* flush dirty sit entries in region of current sit set */
3030 for_each_set_bit_from(segno, bitmap, end) {
3031 int offset, sit_offset;
3032
3033 se = get_seg_entry(sbi, segno);
3034
3035 /* add discard candidates */
3036 if (!(cpc->reason & CP_DISCARD)) {
3037 cpc->trim_start = segno;
3038 add_discard_addrs(sbi, cpc, false);
3039 }
3040
3041 if (to_journal) {
3042 offset = lookup_journal_in_cursum(journal,
3043 SIT_JOURNAL, segno, 1);
3044 f2fs_bug_on(sbi, offset < 0);
3045 segno_in_journal(journal, offset) =
3046 cpu_to_le32(segno);
3047 seg_info_to_raw_sit(se,
3048 &sit_in_journal(journal, offset));
3049 } else {
3050 sit_offset = SIT_ENTRY_OFFSET(sit_i, segno);
3051 seg_info_to_raw_sit(se,
3052 &raw_sit->entries[sit_offset]);
3053 }
3054
3055 __clear_bit(segno, bitmap);
3056 sit_i->dirty_sentries--;
3057 ses->entry_cnt--;
3058 }
3059
3060 if (to_journal)
3061 up_write(&curseg->journal_rwsem);
3062 else
3063 f2fs_put_page(page, 1);
3064
3065 f2fs_bug_on(sbi, ses->entry_cnt);
3066 release_sit_entry_set(ses);
3067 }
3068
3069 f2fs_bug_on(sbi, !list_empty(head));
3070 f2fs_bug_on(sbi, sit_i->dirty_sentries);
3071out:
3072 if (cpc->reason & CP_DISCARD) {
3073 __u64 trim_start = cpc->trim_start;
3074
3075 for (; cpc->trim_start <= cpc->trim_end; cpc->trim_start++)
3076 add_discard_addrs(sbi, cpc, false);
3077
3078 cpc->trim_start = trim_start;
3079 }
3080 mutex_unlock(&sit_i->sentry_lock);
3081
3082 set_prefree_as_free_segments(sbi);
3083}
3084
3085static int build_sit_info(struct f2fs_sb_info *sbi)
3086{
3087 struct f2fs_super_block *raw_super = F2FS_RAW_SUPER(sbi);
3088 struct sit_info *sit_i;
3089 unsigned int sit_segs, start;
3090 char *src_bitmap;
3091 unsigned int bitmap_size;
3092
3093 /* allocate memory for SIT information */
3094 sit_i = kzalloc(sizeof(struct sit_info), GFP_KERNEL);
3095 if (!sit_i)
3096 return -ENOMEM;
3097
3098 SM_I(sbi)->sit_info = sit_i;
3099
3100 sit_i->sentries = kvzalloc(MAIN_SEGS(sbi) *
3101 sizeof(struct seg_entry), GFP_KERNEL);
3102 if (!sit_i->sentries)
3103 return -ENOMEM;
3104
3105 bitmap_size = f2fs_bitmap_size(MAIN_SEGS(sbi));
3106 sit_i->dirty_sentries_bitmap = kvzalloc(bitmap_size, GFP_KERNEL);
3107 if (!sit_i->dirty_sentries_bitmap)
3108 return -ENOMEM;
3109
3110 for (start = 0; start < MAIN_SEGS(sbi); start++) {
3111 sit_i->sentries[start].cur_valid_map
3112 = kzalloc(SIT_VBLOCK_MAP_SIZE, GFP_KERNEL);
3113 sit_i->sentries[start].ckpt_valid_map
3114 = kzalloc(SIT_VBLOCK_MAP_SIZE, GFP_KERNEL);
3115 if (!sit_i->sentries[start].cur_valid_map ||
3116 !sit_i->sentries[start].ckpt_valid_map)
3117 return -ENOMEM;
3118
3119#ifdef CONFIG_F2FS_CHECK_FS
3120 sit_i->sentries[start].cur_valid_map_mir
3121 = kzalloc(SIT_VBLOCK_MAP_SIZE, GFP_KERNEL);
3122 if (!sit_i->sentries[start].cur_valid_map_mir)
3123 return -ENOMEM;
3124#endif
3125
3126 if (f2fs_discard_en(sbi)) {
3127 sit_i->sentries[start].discard_map
3128 = kzalloc(SIT_VBLOCK_MAP_SIZE, GFP_KERNEL);
3129 if (!sit_i->sentries[start].discard_map)
3130 return -ENOMEM;
3131 }
3132 }
3133
3134 sit_i->tmp_map = kzalloc(SIT_VBLOCK_MAP_SIZE, GFP_KERNEL);
3135 if (!sit_i->tmp_map)
3136 return -ENOMEM;
3137
3138 if (sbi->segs_per_sec > 1) {
3139 sit_i->sec_entries = kvzalloc(MAIN_SECS(sbi) *
3140 sizeof(struct sec_entry), GFP_KERNEL);
3141 if (!sit_i->sec_entries)
3142 return -ENOMEM;
3143 }
3144
3145 /* get information related with SIT */
3146 sit_segs = le32_to_cpu(raw_super->segment_count_sit) >> 1;
3147
3148 /* setup SIT bitmap from ckeckpoint pack */
3149 bitmap_size = __bitmap_size(sbi, SIT_BITMAP);
3150 src_bitmap = __bitmap_ptr(sbi, SIT_BITMAP);
3151
3152 sit_i->sit_bitmap = kmemdup(src_bitmap, bitmap_size, GFP_KERNEL);
3153 if (!sit_i->sit_bitmap)
3154 return -ENOMEM;
3155
3156#ifdef CONFIG_F2FS_CHECK_FS
3157 sit_i->sit_bitmap_mir = kmemdup(src_bitmap, bitmap_size, GFP_KERNEL);
3158 if (!sit_i->sit_bitmap_mir)
3159 return -ENOMEM;
3160#endif
3161
3162 /* init SIT information */
3163 sit_i->s_ops = &default_salloc_ops;
3164
3165 sit_i->sit_base_addr = le32_to_cpu(raw_super->sit_blkaddr);
3166 sit_i->sit_blocks = sit_segs << sbi->log_blocks_per_seg;
3167 sit_i->written_valid_blocks = 0;
3168 sit_i->bitmap_size = bitmap_size;
3169 sit_i->dirty_sentries = 0;
3170 sit_i->sents_per_block = SIT_ENTRY_PER_BLOCK;
3171 sit_i->elapsed_time = le64_to_cpu(sbi->ckpt->elapsed_time);
3172 sit_i->mounted_time = ktime_get_real_seconds();
3173 mutex_init(&sit_i->sentry_lock);
3174 return 0;
3175}
3176
3177static int build_free_segmap(struct f2fs_sb_info *sbi)
3178{
3179 struct free_segmap_info *free_i;
3180 unsigned int bitmap_size, sec_bitmap_size;
3181
3182 /* allocate memory for free segmap information */
3183 free_i = kzalloc(sizeof(struct free_segmap_info), GFP_KERNEL);
3184 if (!free_i)
3185 return -ENOMEM;
3186
3187 SM_I(sbi)->free_info = free_i;
3188
3189 bitmap_size = f2fs_bitmap_size(MAIN_SEGS(sbi));
3190 free_i->free_segmap = kvmalloc(bitmap_size, GFP_KERNEL);
3191 if (!free_i->free_segmap)
3192 return -ENOMEM;
3193
3194 sec_bitmap_size = f2fs_bitmap_size(MAIN_SECS(sbi));
3195 free_i->free_secmap = kvmalloc(sec_bitmap_size, GFP_KERNEL);
3196 if (!free_i->free_secmap)
3197 return -ENOMEM;
3198
3199 /* set all segments as dirty temporarily */
3200 memset(free_i->free_segmap, 0xff, bitmap_size);
3201 memset(free_i->free_secmap, 0xff, sec_bitmap_size);
3202
3203 /* init free segmap information */
3204 free_i->start_segno = GET_SEGNO_FROM_SEG0(sbi, MAIN_BLKADDR(sbi));
3205 free_i->free_segments = 0;
3206 free_i->free_sections = 0;
3207 spin_lock_init(&free_i->segmap_lock);
3208 return 0;
3209}

3211static int build_curseg(struct f2fs_sb_info *sbi)
3212{
3213 struct curseg_info *array;
3214 int i;
3215
3216 array = kcalloc(NR_CURSEG_TYPE, sizeof(*array), GFP_KERNEL);
3217 if (!array)
3218 return -ENOMEM;

3238static void build_sit_entries(struct f2fs_sb_info *sbi)
3239{
3240 struct sit_info *sit_i = SIT_I(sbi);
3241 struct curseg_info *curseg = CURSEG_I(sbi, CURSEG_COLD_DATA);
3242 struct f2fs_journal *journal = curseg->journal;
3243 struct seg_entry *se;
3244 struct f2fs_sit_entry sit;
3245 int sit_blk_cnt = SIT_BLK_CNT(sbi);
3246 unsigned int i, start, end;
3247 unsigned int readed, start_blk = 0;
3248
3249 do {
3250 readed = ra_meta_pages(sbi, start_blk, BIO_MAX_PAGES,
3251 META_SIT, true);
3252
3253 start = start_blk * sit_i->sents_per_block;
3254 end = (start_blk + readed) * sit_i->sents_per_block;
3255
3256 for (; start < end && start < MAIN_SEGS(sbi); start++) {
3257 struct f2fs_sit_block *sit_blk;
3258 struct page *page;
3259
3260 se = &sit_i->sentries[start];
3261 page = get_current_sit_page(sbi, start);
3262 sit_blk = (struct f2fs_sit_block *)page_address(page);
3263 sit = sit_blk->entries[SIT_ENTRY_OFFSET(sit_i, start)];
3264 f2fs_put_page(page, 1);
3265
3266 check_block_count(sbi, start, &sit);
3267 seg_info_from_raw_sit(se, &sit);
3268
3269 /* build discard map only one time */
3270 if (f2fs_discard_en(sbi)) {
3271 if (is_set_ckpt_flags(sbi, CP_TRIMMED_FLAG)) {
3272 memset(se->discard_map, 0xff,
3273 SIT_VBLOCK_MAP_SIZE);
3274 } else {
3275 memcpy(se->discard_map,
3276 se->cur_valid_map,
3277 SIT_VBLOCK_MAP_SIZE);
3278 sbi->discard_blks +=
3279 sbi->blocks_per_seg -
3280 se->valid_blocks;
3281 }
3282 }
3283
3284 if (sbi->segs_per_sec > 1)
3285 get_sec_entry(sbi, start)->valid_blocks +=
3286 se->valid_blocks;
3287 }
3288 start_blk += readed;
3289 } while (start_blk < sit_blk_cnt);
3290
3291 down_read(&curseg->journal_rwsem);
3292 for (i = 0; i < sits_in_cursum(journal); i++) {
3293 unsigned int old_valid_blocks;
3294
3295 start = le32_to_cpu(segno_in_journal(journal, i));
3296 se = &sit_i->sentries[start];
3297 sit = sit_in_journal(journal, i);
3298
3299 old_valid_blocks = se->valid_blocks;
3300
3301 check_block_count(sbi, start, &sit);
3302 seg_info_from_raw_sit(se, &sit);
3303
3304 if (f2fs_discard_en(sbi)) {
3305 if (is_set_ckpt_flags(sbi, CP_TRIMMED_FLAG)) {
3306 memset(se->discard_map, 0xff,
3307 SIT_VBLOCK_MAP_SIZE);
3308 } else {
3309 memcpy(se->discard_map, se->cur_valid_map,
3310 SIT_VBLOCK_MAP_SIZE);
3311 sbi->discard_blks += old_valid_blocks -
3312 se->valid_blocks;
3313 }
3314 }
3315
3316 if (sbi->segs_per_sec > 1)
3317 get_sec_entry(sbi, start)->valid_blocks +=
3318 se->valid_blocks - old_valid_blocks;
3319 }
3320 up_read(&curseg->journal_rwsem);
3321}

3323static void init_free_segmap(struct f2fs_sb_info *sbi)
3324{
3325 unsigned int start;
3326 int type;
3327
3328 for (start = 0; start < MAIN_SEGS(sbi); start++) {
3329 struct seg_entry *sentry = get_seg_entry(sbi, start);
3330 if (!sentry->valid_blocks)
3331 __set_free(sbi, start);
3332 else
3333 SIT_I(sbi)->written_valid_blocks +=
3334 sentry->valid_blocks;
3335 }
3336
3337 /* set use the current segments */
3338 for (type = CURSEG_HOT_DATA; type <= CURSEG_COLD_NODE; type++) {
3339 struct curseg_info *curseg_t = CURSEG_I(sbi, type);
3340 __set_test_and_inuse(sbi, curseg_t->segno);
3341 }
3342}

3344static void init_dirty_segmap(struct f2fs_sb_info *sbi)
3345{
3346 struct dirty_seglist_info *dirty_i = DIRTY_I(sbi);
3347 struct free_segmap_info *free_i = FREE_I(sbi);
3348 unsigned int segno = 0, offset = 0;
3349 unsigned short valid_blocks;
3350
3351 while (1) {
3352 /* find dirty segment based on free segmap */
3353 segno = find_next_inuse(free_i, MAIN_SEGS(sbi), offset);
3354 if (segno >= MAIN_SEGS(sbi))
3355 break;
3356 offset = segno + 1;
3357 valid_blocks = get_valid_blocks(sbi, segno, false);
3358 if (valid_blocks == sbi->blocks_per_seg || !valid_blocks)
3359 continue;
3360 if (valid_blocks > sbi->blocks_per_seg) {
3361 f2fs_bug_on(sbi, 1);
3362 continue;
3363 }
3364 mutex_lock(&dirty_i->seglist_lock);
3365 __locate_dirty_segment(sbi, segno, DIRTY);
3366 mutex_unlock(&dirty_i->seglist_lock);
3367 }
3368}

3381static int build_dirty_segmap(struct f2fs_sb_info *sbi)

3383 struct dirty_seglist_info *dirty_i;
3384 unsigned int bitmap_size, i;
3385
3386 /* allocate memory for dirty segments list information */

3388 if (!dirty_i)
3389 return -ENOMEM;

3398 if (!dirty_i->dirty_segmap[i])

3400 }
3401
3402 init_dirty_segmap(sbi);

3406/*
3407 * Update min, max modified time for cost-benefit GC algorithm
3408 */
3409static void init_min_max_mtime(struct f2fs_sb_info *sbi)
3410{
3411 struct sit_info *sit_i = SIT_I(sbi);
3412 unsigned int segno;
3413
3414 mutex_lock(&sit_i->sentry_lock);
3415
3416 sit_i->min_mtime = LLONG_MAX;
3417
3418 for (segno = 0; segno < MAIN_SEGS(sbi); segno += sbi->segs_per_sec) {
3419 unsigned int i;
3420 unsigned long long mtime = 0;
3421
3422 for (i = 0; i < sbi->segs_per_sec; i++)
3423 mtime += get_seg_entry(sbi, segno + i)->mtime;
3424
3425 mtime = div_u64(mtime, sbi->segs_per_sec);
3426
3427 if (sit_i->min_mtime > mtime)
3428 sit_i->min_mtime = mtime;
3429 }
3430 sit_i->max_mtime = get_mtime(sbi);
3431 mutex_unlock(&sit_i->sentry_lock);
3432}

3434int build_segment_manager(struct f2fs_sb_info *sbi)
3435{
3436 struct f2fs_super_block *raw_super = F2FS_RAW_SUPER(sbi);
3437 struct f2fs_checkpoint *ckpt = F2FS_CKPT(sbi);
3438 struct f2fs_sm_info *sm_info;
3439 int err;
3440
3441 sm_info = kzalloc(sizeof(struct f2fs_sm_info), GFP_KERNEL);
3442 if (!sm_info)
3443 return -ENOMEM;
3444
3445 /* init sm info */
3446 sbi->sm_info = sm_info;
3447 sm_info->seg0_blkaddr = le32_to_cpu(raw_super->segment0_blkaddr);
3448 sm_info->main_blkaddr = le32_to_cpu(raw_super->main_blkaddr);
3449 sm_info->segment_count = le32_to_cpu(raw_super->segment_count);
3450 sm_info->reserved_segments = le32_to_cpu(ckpt->rsvd_segment_count);
3451 sm_info->ovp_segments = le32_to_cpu(ckpt->overprov_segment_count);
3452 sm_info->main_segments = le32_to_cpu(raw_super->segment_count_main);
3453 sm_info->ssa_blkaddr = le32_to_cpu(raw_super->ssa_blkaddr);
3454 sm_info->rec_prefree_segments = sm_info->main_segments *
3455 DEF_RECLAIM_PREFREE_SEGMENTS / 100;
3456 if (sm_info->rec_prefree_segments > DEF_MAX_RECLAIM_PREFREE_SEGMENTS)
3457 sm_info->rec_prefree_segments = DEF_MAX_RECLAIM_PREFREE_SEGMENTS;
3458
3459 if (!test_opt(sbi, LFS))
3460 sm_info->ipu_policy = 1 << F2FS_IPU_FSYNC;
3461 sm_info->min_ipu_util = DEF_MIN_IPU_UTIL;
3462 sm_info->min_fsync_blocks = DEF_MIN_FSYNC_BLOCKS;
3463 sm_info->min_hot_blocks = DEF_MIN_HOT_BLOCKS;
3464
3465 sm_info->trim_sections = DEF_BATCHED_TRIM_SECTIONS;
3466
3467 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&sm_info->sit_entry_set);
3468
3469 if (!f2fs_readonly(sbi->sb)) {
3470 err = create_flush_cmd_control(sbi);
3471 if (err)
3472 return err;
3473 }
3474
3475 err = create_discard_cmd_control(sbi);
3476 if (err)
3477 return err;
3478
3479 err = build_sit_info(sbi);
3480 if (err)
3481 return err;
3482 err = build_free_segmap(sbi);
3483 if (err)
3484 return err;
3485 err = build_curseg(sbi);
3486 if (err)
3487 return err;
3488
3489 /* reinit free segmap based on SIT */
3490 build_sit_entries(sbi);
3491
3492 init_free_segmap(sbi);
3493 err = build_dirty_segmap(sbi);
3494 if (err)
3495 return err;
3496
3497 init_min_max_mtime(sbi);
3498 return 0;
3499}

3609int __init create_segment_manager_caches(void)
3610{
3611 discard_entry_slab = f2fs_kmem_cache_create("discard_entry",
3612 sizeof(struct discard_entry));
3613 if (!discard_entry_slab)
3614 goto fail;
3615
3616 discard_cmd_slab = f2fs_kmem_cache_create("discard_cmd",
3617 sizeof(struct discard_cmd));
3618 if (!discard_cmd_slab)
3619 goto destroy_discard_entry;
3620
3621 sit_entry_set_slab = f2fs_kmem_cache_create("sit_entry_set",
3622 sizeof(struct sit_entry_set));
3623 if (!sit_entry_set_slab)
3624 goto destroy_discard_cmd;
3625
3626 inmem_entry_slab = f2fs_kmem_cache_create("inmem_page_entry",
3627 sizeof(struct inmem_pages));
3628 if (!inmem_entry_slab)
3629 goto destroy_sit_entry_set;
3630 return 0;
3631
3632destroy_sit_entry_set:
3633 kmem_cache_destroy(sit_entry_set_slab);
3634destroy_discard_cmd:
3635 kmem_cache_destroy(discard_cmd_slab);
3636destroy_discard_entry:
3637 kmem_cache_destroy(discard_entry_slab);
3638fail:
3639 return -ENOMEM;
3640}
3641
3642void destroy_segment_manager_caches(void)
3643{
3644 kmem_cache_destroy(sit_entry_set_slab);
3645 kmem_cache_destroy(discard_cmd_slab);
3646 kmem_cache_destroy(discard_entry_slab);
3647 kmem_cache_destroy(inmem_entry_slab);
3648}
